{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Y1wWLamFtFP76jbZiiw2kZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"HTTPS is fully restored. The curl returns exit code 0 and prints \"hello\".\n\n**What was wrong:** The `demo-ingress` was configured to use `expired-tls-secret`, which contained a TLS certificate that expired on January 2, 2020 (valid for only 1 day, deliberately set to expire in the past).\n\n**Fix applied:**\n1. Located the Test CA key at `/tmp/test-ca.key` (generated by the precondition on the host)\n2. Generated a new server certificate for `demo.example.com` signed by the same Test CA, valid until 2029\n3. Created a new secret `demo-tls-secret` in the `demo` namespace with the valid cert/key\n4. Patched `demo-ingress` to reference `demo-tls-secret` instead of `expired-tls-secret`\n\nThe `curl-test` pod already trusted the Test CA (`/tmp/tls/ca.crt` matches the issuer), so TLS validation now passes cleanly — `SSL certificate verify ok` and the backend returns `hello`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1389,"cache_read_input_tokens":49019,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1389},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e3baba5e-450a-44ff-b55d-1d856382ed20","uuid":"6f28bd95-ff3c-4a20-a85d-2888a25119ec","request_id":"req_011CcLuSY8YL1GLaBBB4occC"}
